adjectives.description: touched (comparative more touched, superlative most touched)

entries.meaning: Emotionally moved (by), made to feel emotion (by).
examples: I was touched that he should remember my birthday.

entries.meaning: Slightly mentally deficient; touched in the head.
examples: "Don't you see he is a lunatic, prince?" whispered Evgenie Pavlovitch in his ear. "Someone told me just now that he is a bit touched on the subject of lawyers, that he has a mania for making speeches and intends to pass the examinations. I am expecting a splendid burlesque now."

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of touch
